Program: Discovery
Title: Weathering the Storm - lightning
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrysp
Last Broadcast Date: 21 September 2004
Why lightning is an unpredictable power that can cause great havoc. Lightning can cause forest fires, explosions and even death. The second in a series on the world's most extreme weather a look at how lightening forms in the first place, what happens when you get struck by lightning and how can you prevent it? Picture: Lightning bolt, Credit: Thinkstock Show less